tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or at the upper limit of their respective reference ranges. Glycemic control (HbA1c, glucose) is adequate. Renal function (urea, creatinine) and electrolytes are normal, with potassium at the upper reference limit-monitor if clinically indicated. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
